com.weemo.sdk

Interface WeemoCall


  • public interface WeemoCall
    Represents a call. Such an object is created by the SDK on CallCreatedEvent.

      • hangup

        void hangup()
        Hang up the call and stop it. Fires a CallStatusChangedEvent.
        getCallStatus() will be WeemoCall.CallStatus.ENDED.
        Throws:
        WeemoIllegalStateException - if Call is already WeemoCall.CallStatus.ENDED

      • pause

        void pause()
        Pause the call so it can be later resumed.
        Fires a CallStatusChangedEvent.
        getCallStatus() will be WeemoCall.CallStatus.PAUSED.

        WARNING: Not Yet Available !

      • resume

        void resume(WeemoCall.StartingOptions options)
        Resume a WeemoCall.CallStatus.PAUSED call or pick up a WeemoCall.CallStatus.RINGING call, with the provided options.
        Fires a CallStatusChangedEvent.
        A call to getCallStatus() will return WeemoCall.CallStatus.ACTIVE.
        Parameters:
        options - The options to apply
        Throws:
        WeemoIllegalStateException - if Call is already WeemoCall.CallStatus.ACTIVE

      • getCallStatus

        WeemoCall.CallStatus getCallStatus()
        The CallStatus defines the lifecycle of the current call.

        This is the standard workflow in an emitting call :
        WeemoCall.CallStatus.PROCEEDING -> WeemoCall.CallStatus.ACTIVE -> [ WeemoCall.CallStatus.PAUSED -> WeemoCall.CallStatus.ACTIVE ]* -> WeemoCall.CallStatus.ENDED

        This is the standard workflow in a receiving call :
        WeemoCall.CallStatus.RINGING -> WeemoCall.CallStatus.ACTIVE -> [ WeemoCall.CallStatus.PAUSED -> WeemoCall.CallStatus.ACTIVE ]* -> WeemoCall.CallStatus.ENDED

        When a call is being created to call an invalid userID, it's status is, by default, WeemoCall.CallStatus.ENDED
        Returns:
        The status of the call.
